st theorizing, especially in the works of Ernst Bloch, but moreover exposes its critical potential for analysis and solution to reificatory contemporary processes. That is to say, the crisis of capitalism in its post-modern stage: The »unconditional« of the early Romantic period is the antonym to »reification«.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMarxian economics. 0aPhilosophy of naturexHistory. 0aReification. 4aDeutsche Philosophiegeschichte. 4aDeutscher Idealismus. 4aEntfremdung. 4aErnst Bloch. 4aFrühromantik. 4aGeorg Lukács. 4aGesellschaft. 4aKritische Theorie. 4aNatur. 4aNaturphilosophie. 4aPhilosophie. 4aSozialphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh  aCritical Theory.  aGerman History of Philosophy.  aPhilosophy of Nature.  aPhilosophy.  aSocial Philosophy.  aSociety.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2014z9783110370393oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014z9783111025223oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Complete eBook Package 2014-2016z9783110489842oZDB-23-TGP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383762586840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839425862?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839425862423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839425862/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DPHb2014  aZDB-23-TGPb2014  aZDB-23-TGP